##### <span id="index"></span>Search

The (universal) Search page allows the user to search for identities,
employees, user accounts and more, all in one place.

To view the Search: click on the "Search" (magnifying class) menu item.

#### Main page

In the main page you can:

-   Search indexed registrations
-   Search a profile page
-   Rebuild the search index
-   Configure the search index

#### Search indexed registrations

To search for an indexed registration:

1.  Enter a keyword in the search field and press Enter
2.  Click on a result to open it

#### Search for a profile page

The profile page shows the related registrations of an identity. To
search for a profile page:

1.  Enter a keyword in the search field and press Enter
2.  Hover over an result
3.  Click the options menu on the far right
4.  In the menu that opens, click on "Open profile page"

#### Rebuild the search index

<span class="badge rounded-pill bg-info align-text-top">Administrator
only</span>

The search index will automatically update. To manually rebuild/update
it:

1.  Click the options menu in the top right corner
2.  Select "Rebuild"
3.  In the sidepanel that opens, select the type of registration to
    rebuild

#### Configure the search index

<span class="badge rounded-pill bg-info align-text-top">Administrator
only</span>

To configure the search index:

1.  Click the options menu in the top right corner
2.  Select "Search index settings"
3.  In the sidepanel that opens, select the object and attributes that
    need to be indexed
4.  Click "Save and close"
5.  Rebuild the search index
